$ Full Aircraft Static Aeroelastic Trim (SOL 144)
$ Simplified wing + horizontal tail beam model with elevator control surface
$
$ Configuration:
$   - Wing: semi-span 10m, chord 2.0m, sweep 0
$   - H-tail: semi-span 3m, chord 1.0m, at x=8m behind wing LE
$   - Fuselage beam connecting wing to tail
$   - Elevator control surface on H-tail (rear 50% of chord)
$   - Wing structure: 10 CBAR along y=0..10
$   - Tail structure: 6 CBAR along y=0..3 at x=8.5
$   - Fuselage: 4 CBAR along x=0..8.5
$
$ Stiffness design: EI_wing = 1.0e9 N-m^2 (well above divergence)
$ q_div estimate: 3*EI/(e*S*L^2) ~ 3e9/(0.3*20*100) ~ 5e5 >> q=6125
$
$ Flight condition: M=0.3, V=100 m/s, rho=1.225 kg/m3
$ Trim: level flight (Fz = Weight, My_cg = 0)
$ Free variables: ANGLEA, ELEV
$ Fixed: URDD3 = 0 (no vertical acceleration)
$
SOL 144
CEND
$
TITLE = FULL AIRCRAFT STATIC AEROELASTIC TRIM
SPC = 1
TRIM = 1
DISPLACEMENT = ALL
$
